1:1 COMMENT "# io_open.z -- open a file handle and let RAII close it on scope exit."
1:71 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# `io.open` returns `result(file, ioerror)`. The `file` handle owns"
3:68 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# its fd: when `r` goes out of scope, the compiler-emitted destructor"
4:70 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# calls `close(fd)` automatically. Forgetting to close is physically"
5:69 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# impossible."
6:14 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#"
7:2 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# Future phases will add file.read / file.write / file.seek so the"
8:67 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# handle is useful for streaming; for now this example exercises the"
9:69 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# open + RAII path end-to-end."
10:31 EOL "\n"
11:1 EOL "\n"
